715629f-a.title: Manhattan: 140th Street (West) - Riverside Drive
715629f-a.text:
West 140th Street, east from Riverside Drive to Broadway (atop of hill),
showing W.P.A. employees recovering street bed. Partially shown on the
extreme left is the Academy of the Holy Child whileSt. Regis Convent is on
the right. The latter consists of stone and frame buildings bearing No.
628.
May 5, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
